snippet.textDisplay:
I'm definitely now going to watch a 3 hour movie, that I previously was not going to go watch, because of a 4 minute song featured in the title sequence.
Their marketing is working 👍

I've watched some previous bond movies, and enjoyed them, but it's never been something I'd go to the theater to watch. I'm very excited to see the title sequence on the big screen and Billie's voice with all that surround sound and cinematic drama!
I'm sure many other Billie fans are feeling the same way!

I might even watch all the Craig films before No Time To Die just to be up to date on the storyline.

snippet.textDisplay:
People who are saying this is the best bond song.....what the fuck is the matter with you? Seriously? Thanks for enjoying such boring, mediocre music. People like yourselves are why the bar is consistently lowering in all facets of the entertainment industry. Chris Cornell has the best Bond theme HANDS DOWN. Skyfall is a close second.

Seems like Daniel Craig is going out with a whimper rather than a bang. Spectre was so mediocre it was painful. Considering skyfall and casino royale are arguably the best bond films ever made. I have no hopes for this film being decent.
